sky, P.J., The structure of liquid water at an extended hydrophobic surface (1984) J. Chem. Phys., 80, pp. 4448-4455; Lee, K.W., Curtis, L.A., Chen, H., An analytic solution to free-molecule aerosol coagulation (1990) Aerosol. Sci. Technol., 12, pp. 457-462; Limbeck, A., Kulmala, M., Puxbaum, H., Secondary organic aerosol formation in the atmosphere via heterogeneous reaction of gaseous isoprene on acidic particles (2003) Geophys. Res. Lett., 30 (19), p. 1996. , doi:10.1029/2003GL017738; Marti, J., Weber, R., McMurry, P.H., Eisele, F., Tanner, D., Jefferson, A., New particle formation at the remote continental site: Assessing the contribution on SO2 and organic precursors (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102, pp. 6331-6340; McMurry, P., A criterion for new particle formation in the sulfur-rich Atlanta atmosphere (2005) J. Geophys. Res., , doi:10.1029/2005JD005901, in press; O'Dowd, C.D., Aalto, P., Hämeri, K., Kulmala, M., Hoffmann, T., Atmospheric particles from organic vapours (2002) Nature, 416, pp. 497-498; O'Dowd, C.D., Jimenez, J.L., Bahreini, R., Flagan, R.C., Seinfeld, J.H., Hämeri, K., Pirjola, L., Hoffmann, T., Marine aerosol formation from biogenic iodine emissions (2002) Nature, 417, pp. 632-636; Stolzenburg, M., McMurry, P., Sakurai, H., Smith, J., Mauldin III, R., Eisele, F., Clement, C., Growth rates of freshly nucleated atmospheric particles in Atlanta (2005) J. Geophys. Res., , doi:10.1029/2005JD005935, in press; Wehner, B., Philippin, S., Wiedensohler, A., Design and calibration of a thermodenuder with and improved heating unit to measure the size-dependent volatile fraction of aerosol particles (2002) J. Aerosol Sci., 33, pp. 1087-1093","Wehner, B.; Leibniz Institute for Tropospheric Research, Permoserstr. 15, D-04318 Leipzig, Germany; email: birgit@tropos.de",,,,,,,,00948276,,GPRLA,,"English","Geophys. Res. Lett.",Article,Scopus,2-s2.0-27544466393
